text.tspan: Instructions are executed left-to-right,
top-to-bottom, alternating between players.
The starting player alternates each turn.
Move the robot east 2 spaces.
Grab
Grabs the ball or robot in front of
this robot, moving it to this robot's
location. Robots which have been grabbed
cannot move, but can grab, steal and throw
other objects. A robot cannot grab if it
is already holding something.
Grab
Throw 3
If this robot has grabbed the ball or
another robot, throw that object 3 spaces
in the direction this robot is facing. If
there is a robot in the space the object
lands in, that robot automatically grabs
the thrown object.
Throw 3
Steal
If another robot horizontally, vertically
or diagonally adjacent to this robot has
grabbed the ball, steal the ball from
that robot. A robot cannot steal if it is
already holding something.
Steal
Move the robot north 1 space.
Escape
Escape
If this robot has been grabbed by another
robot, it is released and moves one square
in the direction it is facing.
Place instructions in each of the four slots of each of your three
robots. When both players have placed their instructions and pressed
ready, the instructions are executed.
After all instructions have been executed, all buffers are cleared
and players can select the instructions for the next turn.
The objective of the game is to score three goals. You can score a
goal by pushing the ball into the goal, throwing the ball into the
goal, or grabbing the ball and moving into the goal.
When a goal is scored, the turn immediately ends. The ball is
returned to the center of the court; if a robot is in that space
that robot will automatically grab the ball. The position of robots
is not reset when a goal is scored.
X
You can select instructions which cannot be
executed. For example, moving into a wall,
throwing without previously having grabbed
something, or escaping when not grabbed.
Those instructions will be ignored.
